=63818 "><img border=0 src="http://www.darke.net/journalpix/kalestia.jpg"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uartemecium.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Artemecium</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cyber Pimp</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/22/02 5:22:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylummonk.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=247.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice for a growing monk</span><hr size=1> If you want to experience Norrath, most people do it when they're higher level when it's &quot;safe&quot; to do so.<br><br>It is ALOT easier to follow this hunting guide, but you'll be inexperienced at dungeons.<br><br>Newbie area&gt;Oasis&gt;Ill Omen&gt; FM &gt; OT &gt; DL &gt; Velks<br><br>However you really should stick to it if you want to get higher faster with more power yada yada yada.  I know there's other places out there with faster exp in your level range (CT, Dalnir, WW) However most of those are BYOG and you don't have that option so I would stick with Ill Omen until 30, then FM until 33ish then OT until 40 then DL to high 40s. <p><hr>Artemecium Valiant, 53 Pathfinder<br>Nibl Heim, 53 Cavalier<hr></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utanilium.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tanilium</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/22/02 7:54:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylummonk.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=247.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice for a growing monk</span><hr size=1> mid to late 20's are IMO, the worst for a monk. lvl 30 you get flying kick, and you can do a lot more. The xtra damage helps out, and you begin to feel viable.<br><br>If I were you, honest, I'd find a good partner to that plays during your time.  I generally prefer to duo if I can. I've found my best duo partners to be bards/monks/shaman/necros in no particular order.<br><br>While it's easy to do get exp doing outdoor mob zones, I'd make sure you spend time learning to pull dungeons. Despite it's difficulty, Dalnir is a very good place to figure out how to pull casters (!!). Cazic is a good spot to learn pulling as well. Also, you can loot the FS and sell to the ogre merchants. =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ugenji27.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Genji27</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/22/02 5:23:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylummonk.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=247.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice for a growing monk</span><hr size=1> Cute sig Kalestia. Wish it was color. Dragonscar eh? Any relationship to you Tani?<br><br>If you solo a lot, remember bind wounds and instill doubt are your friends. You can duo well with other classes too, but the classes that can heal (even ghetto necro heal) and enchanters (yeah right, like you'll ever find an ungrouped enchanter =P) are better to duo with.<br><br>And I didn't camp Raster in 3 foot snowdrifts, uphill, and without food or water AND LIKED IT, I was an evil little leezurd zergling and knocked off Zephyl =P <p>Genji<BR>Zerg Thane</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucaelynncoppertrail.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caelynn Coppertrail</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cyber Pimp</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/23/02 3:17:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylummonk.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=247.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.crocker.com/~denise/amflag.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice for a growing monk</span><hr size=1> /rude Genji.. I've camped that bastage twice.. never.. again.  Cheat.  Get a group together (YES, Zephyl can be done with ONE group), and kick the snot outta that boy.<br><br>Caelynn<br>Monkette <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucaelynncoppertrail.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caelynn Coppertrail</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cyber Pimp</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/23/02 3:18:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylummonk.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=247.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.crocker.com/~denise/amflag.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice for a growing monk</span><hr size=1> More advice for a growing monk.. never agree to help a cleric camp ragefire.  It sucks your life away.  Though, with the change comming to ragefire, they may start bribing rangers instead of monks..<br><br>Caelynn<br>Monkette <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ugenji27.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Genji27</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/23/02 6:02:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylummonk.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=247.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice for a growing monk</span><hr size=1> /cry<br>Cae gave me the finger just cause I offed Zephyl =/ <p>Genji<BR>Zerg Thane</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udobbanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dobbanz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/12/02 4:03:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylummonk.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=247.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice for a growing monk</span><hr size=1> At 25 I think you can go to the garg island on oot and still get good exp from the gargs not to  mention phenominal loot for that level with the stackable eyes that weigh 0.1 and sell for 7 to 8pp each /drool! I made 600pp in loot from there going to 27 (yeah i know the gargs start to go low blue then but I was after cash lol) Then I went to loio and soloed the 4 spawn of goblins in the tower that you find by going to the mill then go straight past the undead ruins and youll see it there. It was great exp to 28 whenI moved to the sarnak fort and soloed there till 29 now I am 30 and got that level in Mars Seru. This zone is godly for a solo monk. 29 flew by and anytime those stupid zelinaks agrood me from the other side of the zone I would just fd till it left np. There is even a monk guild hall in Sanctus Seru if you raise your faction by killing these people that are in several enclaves in the zone. I forget there names but they are the only human mobs there and they are a lot like higher level dervs lol. They can be all sorts of classes but they give you positive faction with all the Sanctus Seru groups so go nuts and good luck.<br><br>Traab &quot;Love Machine&quot; Fellhammer<br>Human Mob Compactor of the 30th Cycle<br>And Almost Too Sexy To Live!<br><br>&quot;I almost swallowed my tounge when I saw my flying kick damage for the first time lol.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr>